    20 2 acc

    25 def user_profile(code) do
    26 # body = "client_id=#{@client_id}&client_secret=#{@client_secret}&code=#{code}&redirect_uri=#{@redirect_uri}"
    27 # post("access_token?#{body}",%{})

    37 0 try do

    39 %{status: 200, body: %{"error" => error, "error_description" => description}} ->
    40 0 {:error, "#{error}: #{description}"}

    42 %{status: 200, body: %{"access_token" => access_token, "token_type" => "bearer"}} ->
    43 0 user_info(access_token)

    46 0 e ->
    47 0 e |> handle_tesla_error

    55
    56 0 headers = %{"Accept" => "application/vnd.github.jean-grey-preview+json"}
    57 0 query = [access_token: access_token]

    59 0 try do
    60 0 case get(url, query: query, headers: headers) do
    61 %{status: 200, body: body} ->
    62 0 body = body |> Map.merge(%{"access_token" => access_token})
    63 {:ok, body}

    69 {:error, "OAuth2 Github: " <> body}

    71 _ ->

    20 def follow(%User{id: user_id}, %User{id: follower_id}) do

    22 98 {:ok, _follow_user} <- ORM.find(User, follower_id) do

    0 defmodule MastaniServer.CMS.Delegate.ArticleCURD do
    1 import Ecto.Query, warn: false
    2 import MastaniServer.CMS.Utils.Matcher
    3 import Helper.Utils, only: [done: 1]
    4 import ShortMaps

    13 @doc """
    14 get paged post / job ...
    15 """
    16 def paged_contents(queryable, filter) do
    17 44 normal_content_fr = filter |> Map.merge(QueryBuilder.default_article_filters())
    18
    19 queryable
    20 |> ORM.find_all(normal_content_fr)
    21 44 |> add_pin_contents_ifneed(queryable, filter)
    22 end
    23
    24 # only first page need pin contents
    25 defp add_pin_contents_ifneed(contents, queryable, filter) do
    26 44 with {:ok, normal_contents} <- contents,
    27 44 true <- 1 == Map.get(normal_contents, :page_number) do
    28 38 pin_content_fr = filter |> Map.merge(%{pin: true})
    29 38 {:ok, pined_content} = queryable |> ORM.find_all(pin_content_fr)
    30
    31 38 case pined_content |> Map.get(:total_count) do
    32 0 ->
    33 35 contents
    34
    35 _ ->
    36 3 pind_entries = pined_content |> Map.get(:entries)
    37 3 normal_entries = normal_contents |> Map.get(:entries)
    38
    39 3 normal_count = normal_contents |> Map.get(:total_count)
    40 3 pind_count = pined_content |> Map.get(:total_count)
    41
    42 normal_contents
    43 |> Map.put(:entries, pind_entries ++ normal_entries)
    44 |> Map.put(:total_count, pind_count + normal_count)
    45 3 |> done
    46 end
    47 else
    48 _error ->
    49 6 contents
    50 end
    51 end

    2 set / unset operations for Article-like resource

    16 def set_flag(queryable, id, %{pin: _} = attrs, %User{} = _user) do

    18 end
    19
    20 def set_flag(queryable, id, %{trash: _} = attrs, %User{} = _user) do
    21 10 queryable |> ORM.find_update(id, attrs)
    22 end
    23
    24 def set_community(%Community{id: community_id}, thread, content_id) when valid_thread(thread) do
    25 31 with {:ok, action} <- match_action(thread, :community),
    26 31 {:ok, content} <- ORM.find(action.target, content_id, preload: :communities),
    27 31 {:ok, community} <- ORM.find(action.reactor, community_id) do
    28 content
    29 |> Ecto.Changeset.change()
    30 31 |> Ecto.Changeset.put_assoc(:communities, content.communities ++ [community])
    31 31 |> Repo.update()
    32 end
    33 end
    34
    35 def unset_community(%Community{id: community_id}, thread, content_id)
    36 when valid_thread(thread) do
    37 1 with {:ok, action} <- match_action(thread, :community),
    38 1 {:ok, content} <- ORM.find(action.target, content_id, preload: :communities),
    39 1 {:ok, community} <- ORM.find(action.reactor, community_id) do
    40 content
    41 |> Ecto.Changeset.change()
    42 1 |> Ecto.Changeset.put_assoc(:communities, content.communities -- [community])
    43 1 |> Repo.update()
    44 end
    45 end
    46
    47 @doc """
    48 set tag for post / tuts / videos ...
    49 """
    50 # check community first
    51 def set_tag(%Community{id: communitId}, thread, %Tag{id: tag_id}, content_id) do
    52 10 with {:ok, action} <- match_action(thread, :tag),
    53 10 {:ok, content} <- ORM.find(action.target, content_id, preload: :tags),
    54 10 {:ok, tag} <- ORM.find(action.reactor, tag_id) do
    55 10 case tag_in_community_thread?(%Community{id: communitId}, thread, tag) do
    56 true ->
    57 content
    58 |> Ecto.Changeset.change()
    59 8 |> Ecto.Changeset.put_assoc(:tags, content.tags ++ [tag])
    60 8 |> Repo.update()
    61
    62 _ ->
    63 {:error, message: "Tag,Community,Thread not match", code: ecode(:custom)}
    64 end
    65 end
    66 end
    67
    68 def unset_tag(thread, %Tag{id: tag_id}, content_id) when valid_thread(thread) do
    69 1 with {:ok, action} <- match_action(thread, :tag),
    70 1 {:ok, content} <- ORM.find(action.target, content_id, preload: :tags),

    72 content
    73 |> Ecto.Changeset.change()
    74 1 |> Ecto.Changeset.put_assoc(:tags, content.tags -- [tag])
    75 1 |> Repo.update()
    76 end
    77 end
    78
    79 # make sure the reuest tag is in the current community thread
    80 # example: you can't set a other thread tag to this thread's article
    81 defp tag_in_community_thread?(%Community{id: communityId}, thread, tag) do
    82 10 with {:ok, community} <- ORM.find(Community, communityId) do
    83 10 matched_tags =
    84 Tag
    85 10 |> where([t], t.community_id == ^community.id)
    86 # |> where([t], t.thread == ^(to_string(thread) |> String.upcase()))
    87 10 |> where([t], t.thread == ^to_string(thread))
    88 |> Repo.all()
    89
    90 10 tag in matched_tags
    91 end
    92 end

    0 defmodule MastaniServer.CMS.Delegate.ArticleReaction do
    1 @moduledoc """
    2 reaction[favorite, star, watch ...] on article [post, job, video...]
    3 """
    4 import Helper.Utils, only: [done: 1, done: 2]
    5 import MastaniServer.CMS.Utils.Matcher
    6 import Ecto.Query, warn: false
    7 import Helper.ErrorCode
    8
    9 alias Helper.ORM
    10 alias MastaniServer.{Accounts, Repo}
    11
    12 alias Accounts.User
    13 alias Ecto.Multi
    14
    15 @doc """
    16 favorite / star / watch CMS contents like post / tuts / video ...
    17 """
    18 # when valid_reaction(thread, react) do
    19 def reaction(thread, react, content_id, %User{id: user_id}) do
    20 139 with {:ok, action} <- match_action(thread, react),
    21 139 {:ok, content} <- ORM.find(action.target, content_id, preload: [author: :user]),
    22 139 {:ok, user} <- ORM.find(Accounts.User, user_id) do
    23 Multi.new()
    24 |> Multi.run(:create_reaction_record, fn _ ->
    25 139 create_reaction_record(action, user, thread, content)
    26 end)
    27 |> Multi.run(:add_achievement, fn _ ->
    28 139 achiever_id = content.author.user_id
    29 139 Accounts.achieve(%User{id: achiever_id}, :add, react)
    30 end)
    31 |> Repo.transaction()
    32 139 |> reaction_result()
    33 end
    34 end
    35
    36 139 defp reaction_result({:ok, %{create_reaction_record: result}}), do: result |> done()
    37
    38 defp reaction_result({:error, :create_reaction_record, _result, _steps}),
    39 do: {:error, [message: "create reaction fails", code: ecode(:react_fails)]}
    40
    41 defp reaction_result({:error, :add_achievement, _result, _steps}),

    0 defmodule MastaniServer.CMS.Delegate.PassportCURD do
    1 @moduledoc """
    2 passport curd
    3 """
    4 import Helper.Utils, only: [done: 1, deep_merge: 2]
    5 import Ecto.Query, warn: false
    6 import ShortMaps
    7
    8 alias Helper.{NestedFilter, ORM}
    9 alias MastaniServer.CMS.Passport, as: UserPasport
    10 alias MastaniServer.{Accounts, Repo}
    11
    12 # https://medium.com/front-end-hacking/use-github-oauth-as-your-sso-seamlessly-with-react-3e2e3b358fa1
    13 # http://www.ubazu.com/using-postgres-jsonb-columns-in-ecto
    14 # http://www.ubazu.com/using-postgres-jsonb-columns-in-ecto
    15
    16 def list_passports(community, key) do
    17 UserPasport
    18 3 |> where([p], fragment("(?->?->>?)::boolean = ?", p.rules, ^community, ^key, true))
    19 |> Repo.all()
    20 3 |> done
    21 end
    22
    23 @doc """
    24 return a user's passport in CMS context
    25 """
    26 def get_passport(%Accounts.User{} = user) do
    27 211 with {:ok, passport} <- ORM.find_by(UserPasport, user_id: user.id) do
    28 79 {:ok, passport.rules}
    29 end
    30 end
    31
    32 # TODO passport should be public utils
    33 @doc """
    34 insert or update a user's passport in CMS context
    35 """
    36 def stamp_passport(rules, %Accounts.User{id: user_id}) do
    37 139 case ORM.find_by(UserPasport, user_id: user_id) do
    38 {:ok, passport} ->
    39 5 rules = passport.rules |> deep_merge(rules) |> reject_invalid_rules
    40 5 passport |> ORM.update(~m(rules)a)
    41
    42 {:error, _} ->
    43 134 rules = rules |> reject_invalid_rules
    44 134 UserPasport |> ORM.create(~m(user_id rules)a)
    45 end
    46 end
    47
    48 def erase_passport(rules, %Accounts.User{id: user_id}) when is_list(rules) do
    49 4 with {:ok, passport} <- ORM.find_by(UserPasport, user_id: user_id) do
    50 4 case pop_in(passport.rules, rules) do
    51 {nil, _} ->
    52 3 {:error, "#{rules} not found"}
    53
    54 {_, lefts} ->
    55 1 passport |> ORM.update(%{rules: lefts})
    56 end
    57 end
    58 end
    59
    60 def delete_passport(%Accounts.User{id: user_id}) do
    61 1 ORM.findby_delete(UserPasport, ~m(user_id)a)
    62 end
    63
    64 defp reject_invalid_rules(rules) when is_map(rules) do
    65 139 rules |> NestedFilter.drop_by_value([false]) |> reject_empty_values
    66 end
    67
    68 defp reject_empty_values(map) when is_map(map) do
    69 139 for {k, v} <- map, v != %{}, into: %{}, do: {k, v}
    70 end

    59 defp fetch_mails(user, queryable, %{page: page, size: size, read: read}) do
    60 8 {:ok, last_fetch_time} = get_last_fetch_time(queryable, read, user)
    61
    62 queryable

    64 |> where([m], m.inserted_at > ^last_fetch_time)
    65 8 |> where([m], m.read == ^read)
    66 |> ORM.paginater(~m(page size)a)
    67 8 |> done()

    70 defp fetch_mails_and_delete(user, queryable, %{page: page, size: size, read: read}) do
    71 60 {:ok, last_fetch_time} = get_last_fetch_time(queryable, read, user)
    72
    73 60 query =
    74 queryable
    75 60 |> where([m], m.to_user_id == ^user.id)
    76 |> where([m], m.inserted_at > ^last_fetch_time)
    77 60 |> where([m], m.read == ^read)
    78
    79 60 mails =
    80 query
    81 60 |> order_by(desc: :inserted_at)
    82 |> ORM.paginater(~m(page size)a)
    83 |> done()
    84
    85 60 delete_items(query, mails)
    86
    87 60 mails
    88 end

    173 94 long_long_ago = Timex.shift(Timex.now(), years: -10)
    174
    175 94 with {:ok, record} <- Record |> ORM.find_by(user_id: user_id) do
    176 record
    177 |> has_valid_value(record_key)
    178 41 |> case do
    179 false ->
    180 {:ok, long_long_ago}
    181
    182 true ->
    183 record
    184 |> Map.get(record_key)
    185 16 |> Map.get(timekey, to_string(long_long_ago))
    186 16 |> NaiveDateTime.from_iso8601()

    196 defp delete_items(queryable, {:ok, %{entries: entries}}) do
    197 # delete_all only support queryable and where syntax
    198 # TODO: move logic to queue job
    199
    200 19 first_id = entries |> List.first() |> Map.get(:id)
    201 19 last_id = entries |> List.last() |> Map.get(:id)
    202
    203 19 min_id = Enum.min([first_id, last_id])
    204 19 max_id = Enum.max([first_id, last_id])
    205
    206 queryable
    207 19 |> where([m], m.id >= ^min_id and m.id <= ^max_id)
    208 19 |> Repo.delete_all()
    209 end

    211 defp do_mark_read_all(queryable, %User{} = user) do
    212 4 query =
    213 queryable
    214 4 |> where([m], m.to_user_id == ^user.id)
    215
    216 4 try do
    217 4 Repo.update_all(
    218 query,
    219 set: [read: true]
    220 )
    221
    222 {:ok, %{status: true}}
    223 rescue
    224 _ -> {:error, %{status: false}}
    225 end
    226 end

    75 defp to_contrubutes_map(data) do
    76 4 end_date = Timex.today()
    77 4 start_date = Timex.shift(Timex.today(), months: -6)
    78 4 total_count = Enum.reduce(data, 0, &(&1.count + &2))
    79
    80 4 records = to_contribute_records(data)
    81
    82 4 ~m(start_date end_date total_count records)a

    88 4 %{
    89 date: convert_date(date),
    90 count: count
    91 }
    92 end)
    93 end
    94
    95 # 返回 count 数组，方便前端绘图
    96 # example:
    97 # from: [0,0,0,0,0,0]
    98 # to: [0,30,3,8,0,0]
    99 # 如果 7 天都有 count, 不用计算直接 map 返回
    100 defp to_counts_digest(record, days: count) do
    101 0 case length(record) == @community_contribute_days + 1 do
    102 true ->
    103 0 Enum.map(record, & &1.count)
    104
    105 false ->
    106 0 today = Timex.today() |> Date.to_erl()
    107 0 return_count = abs(count) + 1
    108 0 enmpty_tuple = return_count |> repeat(0) |> List.to_tuple()
    109
    110 0 results =
    111 Enum.reduce(record, enmpty_tuple, fn record, acc ->
    112 0 diff = Timex.diff(Timex.to_date(record.date), today, :days)
    113 0 index = diff + abs(count)
    114
    115 0 put_elem(acc, index, record.count)
    116 end)
    117
    118 0 results |> Tuple.to_list()
    119 end
    120 end

    0 defmodule MastaniServer.Statistics.Delegate.Throttle do
    1 import Ecto.Query, warn: false
    2 import ShortMaps
    3
    4 alias MastaniServer.Accounts.User
    5 alias MastaniServer.Statistics.PublishThrottle
    6 alias Helper.{ORM}
    7
    8 def log_publish_action(%User{id: user_id}) do
    9 26 cur_date = Timex.today() |> Date.to_iso8601()
    10 26 cur_datetime = DateTime.utc_now() |> DateTime.to_iso8601()
    11
    12 26 last_publish_time = cur_datetime
    13 26 publish_hour = cur_datetime
    14 26 publish_date = cur_date
    15
    16 26 case PublishThrottle |> ORM.find_by(~m(user_id)a) do
    17 {:ok, record} ->
    18 4 date_count = record.date_count + 1
    19 4 hour_count = record.hour_count + 1
    20
    21 4 attrs = ~m(user_id publish_date publish_hour date_count hour_count last_publish_time)a
    22 4 record |> ORM.update(attrs)
    23
    24 {:error, _} ->
    25 22 date_count = 1
    26 22 hour_count = 1
    27 22 attrs = ~m(user_id publish_date publish_hour date_count hour_count last_publish_time)a
    28 22 PublishThrottle |> ORM.create(attrs)
    29 end
    30 end
    31
    32 # auto run check for same hour / day
    33 def load_throttle_record(%User{id: user_id}) do
    34 17 with {:ok, record} <- PublishThrottle |> ORM.find_by(~m(user_id)a) do
    35 9 date_count = if is_same_day?(record.publish_date), do: record.date_count, else: 0
    36 9 hour_count = if is_same_hour?(record.publish_hour), do: record.hour_count, else: 0
    37
    38 9 case date_count !== 0 or hour_count !== 0 do
    39 true ->
    40 9 cur_date = Timex.today() |> Date.to_iso8601()
    41 9 cur_datetime = DateTime.utc_now() |> DateTime.to_iso8601()
    42
    43 9 publish_hour = cur_datetime
    44 9 publish_date = cur_date
    45
    46 9 attrs = ~m(publish_date publish_hour date_count hour_count)a
    47 9 record |> ORM.update(attrs)
    48
    49 false ->
    50 {:ok, record}
    51 end
    52 end
    53 end
    54
    55 defp is_same_day?(datetime) do
    56 18 datetime |> Timex.to_date() |> Timex.equal?(Timex.to_date(Timex.now()))
    57 end
    58
    59 defp is_same_hour?(datetime) do
    60 9 {_date, {record_hour, _min, _sec}} = datetime |> Timex.to_erl()

    0 defmodule MastaniServerWeb.UserSocket do
    1 use Phoenix.Socket
    2
    3 ## Channels
    4 # channel "room:*", MastaniServerWeb.RoomChannel
    5
    6 ## Transports
    7 transport(:websocket, Phoenix.Transports.WebSocket)
    8 # transport :longpoll, Phoenix.Transports.LongPoll
    9
    10 # Socket params are passed from the client and can
    11 # be used to verify and authenticate a user. After
    12 # verification, you can put default assigns into
    13 # the socket that will be set for all channels, ie
    14 #
    15 # {:ok, assign(socket, :user_id, verified_user_id)}
    16 #
    17 # To deny connection, return `:error`.
    18 #
    19 # See `Phoenix.Token` documentation for examples in
    20 # performing token verification on connect.
    21 def connect(_params, socket) do
    22 {:ok, socket}
    23 end
    24
    25 # Socket id's are topics that allow you to identify all sockets for a given user:
    26 #
    27 # def id(socket), do: "user_socket:#{socket.assigns.user_id}"
    28 #
    29 # Would allow you to broadcast a "disconnect" event and terminate
    30 # all active sockets and channels for a given user:
    31 #
    32 # MastaniServerWeb.Endpoint.broadcast("user_socket:#{user.id}", "disconnect", %{})
    33 #
    34 # Returning `nil` makes this socket anonymous.
    35 def id(_socket), do: nil
    36 end

    328 field :posts_count, :integer do
    329 resolve(fn community, _args, %{context: %{loader: loader}} ->
    330 loader
    331 0 |> Dataloader.load(CMS, {:one, CMS.Post}, posts_count: community.id)
    332 0 |> on_load(fn loader ->
    333 0 {:ok, Dataloader.get(loader, CMS, {:one, CMS.Post}, posts_count: community.id)}
    334 end)
    335 end)
    336 end

    8
    9 Finally, if the test case interacts with the database,
    10 it cannot be async. For this reason, every test runs
    11 inside a transaction which is reset at the beginning
    12 of the test unless the test case is marked as async.
    13 """

    29
    30 0 unless tags[:async] do
    31 0 Ecto.Adapters.SQL.Sandbox.mode(MastaniServer.Repo, {:shared, self()})

    35 end

    37 @doc """
    38 A helper that transform changeset errors to a map of messages.
    39
    40 assert {:error, changeset} = Accounts.create_user(%{password: "short"})
    41 assert "password is too short" in errors_on(changeset).password
    42 assert %{password: ["password is too short"]} = errors_on(changeset)
    43
    44 """
    45 def errors_on(changeset) do
    46 0 Ecto.Changeset.traverse_errors(changeset, fn {message, opts} ->
    47 0 Enum.reduce(opts, message, fn {key, value}, acc ->
    48 0 String.replace(acc, "%{#{key}}", to_string(value))
    49 end)
    50 end)
    51 end
